articles.description: Ivy Smith Jr. scored the final seven points and Grambling held off Prairie View A&M, 90-85 on Saturday night to win their ninth straight game and move into a first-place tie in the Southwestern Conference.
articles.headline: Grambling beats Prairie View 90-85, moves into 1st-place tie

articles.description: Justin Tillman ripped the nets for a career-high 37 points, including seven of VCU's nine points in overtime, and the Rams pulled out an 88-84 victory over Dayton on Saturday.
articles.headline: Tillman powers VCU to 88-84 OT win over Dayton

images.caption: After VCU's Issac Vann knocks down a 3-pointer late in the first half, Jalen Crutcher heaves up a shot and gets it to go at the buzzer.
images.name: Dayton's Crutcher hits shot from beyond half court

articles.description: Miles Bridges pulls up from deep and drills it as No. 4 Michigan State edges No. 3 Purdue 68-65. Listen and look at the sights and sounds of the parties involved.
articles.headline: Bridges' game-winning triple from all the angles

images.caption: Miles Bridges pulls up from deep and drills it as No. 4 Michigan State edges No. 3 Purdue 68-65. Listen and look at the sights and sounds of the parties involved.
images.name: Bridges' game-winning triple from all the angles

articles.description: Kerry Blackshear Jr. scored on a putback with 5.8 seconds left and Virginia Tech spoiled No. 2 Virginia's opportunity to climb to No. 1 with a 61-60 overtime victory Saturday night.
articles.headline: Blackshear's putback lift Hokies past No. 2 Virginia in OT

images.caption: Justin Robinson says the upset win over No. 2 Virginia was huge for his team as they get deeper into ACC play.
images.name: VT's Robinson: 'This road win was huge'
